<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="286" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d286">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119 Military Clauses/1:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany (<persName corresp="#p_SFM1" type="to">Sackett</persName>)</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-17T17:00:00-04:00">August 17,
                                    1932—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>97. The United Press despatch from Berlin reports that Germany and France
                            are on the point of initiating direct negotiations concerning the
                            limitations placed on German armaments by the Treaty of Versailles.<note n="40" xml:id="d286fn40">
                                <hi rend="italic">Treaties, Conventions, etc., Between the United
                                    States of America and Other Powers</hi>, 1910–1923 (Washington,
                                Government Printing Office, 1923), vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 3329.</note> The first conversations, according to
                            this report, are expected to begin some time next week upon the return
                            to Berlin of the French Ambassador.<note n="41" xml:id="d286fn41">
                                <persName corresp="#p_FA1">André François-Poncet</persName>.</note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Do you have any information which would confirm this story?</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>